  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Pest control technician",
  "description": "<p>Hey bros! LOOKING FOR EXPERIENCED 3YEARS AND ABOVE PEST CONTROL TECH. \n\n\n\n+Drive home van\n\n+Flexible hours\n\n\n\nKey Responsibilities (Job Scope):\n\n\n\n· Conduct thorough site inspections and assessments to identify pest infestations (e.g., rodents, termites, cockroaches, mosquitoes, bed bugs) and conducive conditions.\n\n· Develop, propose, and execute targeted Integrated Pest Management (IPM) treatment plans using a variety of methods (chemical, non-chemical, baiting, trapping, exclusion).\n\n· Safely handle, apply, and store pesticides and chemicals in strict compliance with Singapore's National Environment Agency (NEA) guidelines and Environmental Public Health (EPH) Act.\n\n· Prepare detailed and accurate service reports, treatment records, recommendations, and certificates using digital or mobile systems.\n\n· Provide expert advice to clients on pest prevention measures and follow-up schedules.\n\n· Maintain, calibrate, and ensure the good condition of all pest control equipment and tools.\n\n· Respond promptly to urgent service calls and customer feedback.\n\n· Assist in training and guiding junior technicians on best practices and safety protocols.\n\n· Uphold the highest standards of professionalism, customer service, and safety at all client sites.\n\n\n\nRequirements:\n\n\n\n· Mandatory: Valid Singapore Pest Control Technician Licence issued by the National Environment Agency (NEA).\n\n· Minimum of 3 years of hands-on field experience in pest control within Singapore.\n\n· Strong knowledge of local pest species, their biology, and behavior.\n\n· In-depth understanding of NEA regulations, SAFE management procedures, and the use of approved pesticides.\n\n· Proven ability to diagnose complex pest issues and implement effective solutions.\n\n· Excellent communication and interpersonal skills, with the ability to explain technical details to clients clearly.\n\n· Physically fit to handle equipment, work in various environments, and sometimes in confined spaces.\n\n· Possess a Class 3 driving license is a strong advantage.\n\n· Responsible, punctual, honest, and with a strong service mindset. </p>",
